-- AVI, BHP, Pick n Pay, Silverbridge May Move: South African Equity Preview
-- B y   G a r t h   T h e u n i s s e n   a n d   R e n e e   B o n o r c h i s
-- 2010-10-20T05:29:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-20/avi-bhp-pick-n-pay-silverbridge-may-move-south-african-equity-preview.html
The following is a list of companies
whose shares may have unusual price changes in  South Africa .
Stock symbols are in parentheses after company names and prices
are from the last close.  South Africa’s  FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index  fell 173.97,
or 0.6 percent, to 30,003.08 at the 5 p.m. close in
Johannesburg.  AVI Ltd.  (AVI SJ): The producer and distributor of consumer
goods including food and cosmetics holds its annual general
meeting. The company’s stock rose 35 cents, or 1.3 percent, to
27.20 rand.  BHP Billiton Ltd.  (BIL SJ): The world’s largest mining
company said first-quarter iron-ore production rose 6 percent as
it expands mining in Western Australia to meet steel demand. BHP
dropped 3.65 rand, or 1.5 percent, to 234.35 rand.  Pick n Pay Stores Ltd.  (PIK SJ): South Africa’s second-
largest food retailer publishes first-half earnings. The Cape
Town-based company’s stock lost 29 cents, or 0.7 percent, to
42.69 rand.  Silverbridge Holdings Ltd.  (SVB SJ): The computer software
company said net income decreased to 1.14 million rand
($164,000) in the six months to end-August, compared with 5.15
million rand in the same period the previous year. The company’s
stock was unchanged at 1.90 rand.  Shares or American depositary receipts of the following
South African companies closed as follows:  Anglo American Plc  (AAUK US) fell 4.4 percent to $21.71.
 AngloGold Ashanti Ltd . (AU US) dropped 3.8 percent to $45.25.
BHP Billiton Ltd. (BBL US) shed 4.1 percent to $66.84.  DRDGold
Ltd . (DROOY US) lost 7.6 percent to $4.87.  Gold Fields Ltd . (GFI
US) retreated 4 percent to $15.07.  Harmony Gold Mining Co . (HMY
US) slipped 4 percent to $10.75. Impala Platinum Holdings (IMPUY
US) fell 4 percent to $27.45.  Sappi Ltd . (SPP US) slumped 2
percent to $4.94.  Sasol Ltd . (SSL US) lost 1.5 percent to
$45.50.  To contact the reporters on this story:
